Interface IManagerEventClient

    • Method Detail

      • getHandledEvents

        int getHandledEvents()
        Gets flags of all handled events. Return ManagerEvent.EVENT_NONE (0) if client does not have any dynamic content. Warning: returned value must be constant.
        Returns:
        Integer with flags of events that client wants to be notified about.

      • onIncomingEvent

        void onIncomingEvent(int pEventFlags,
                   Object pEventInfo)
        Called when some flags of a new event match flags returned by getHandledEvents(). Will be always called from UI thread.
        Parameters:
        pEventFlags - Flags of new event.
        pEventInfo - Optional Object with details of this event - can be null.
